label day4:
    call day4_morning


    return

label day4_morning:
    
    "The vampires wake up."

    f "Hey, sis, my wings are still fully numb!"

    r "Oh, that's... cool."

    "Remilia looks over to Flandre, then pauses."

    f "Um, sis?"

    "Remilia looks away for a moment, and then back."

    r "Can I look at your wings real quick?"

    f "Are they worse?"

    r "Um... I think it might be a little worse. I want to make sure."

    f "...Ok."

    "Remilia flies over behind Flandre."

    r "The holes are bigger."

    f "How much bigger?"

    r "Like, a little bit? I guess? I think Patchouli would be a better person to ask."

    f "Ok. Let's go. Thank you for telling me."

    r "Mhm."

    "They go to the library."

    r "Hey, Patchouli."

    p "Hi. Um, did something happen?"

    r "It looks like her wings deteriorated."

    p "Oh. Let me see."

    "Flandre walks over and Patchouli looks."

    p "Yes. They did. Odd, this is a sudden change."

    f "Is it bad?"

    p "It is not preferable. But also not outside of expectations. I planned on experimenting with them all day, I have time to look into it."

    f "Ok."

    "Patchouli reapplies the numb spell, then looks over to Remilia."

    p "Are you going to watch all night again?"

    r "No. I don't think that's necessary anymore."

    f "Was it ever?"

    r "Yes. You were vulnerable in that position."

    f "Oh, right. You were worried about her doing weird stuff."

    r "Oh, sure. Whatever."

    p "You can read a book."

    r "No. Do you think you could unlock the front door? I want to go outside for a bit."

    p "Unlock?"

    r "Yes."

    p "I never locked it."

    r "What? I thought you locked us in?"

    p "No."

    r "I guess I never checked. You would've just let us go?"

    p "Yes. I would rather not deal with trapped, angry vampires. I would've let you leave, even if it would ruin my study project."

    f "What about the explody thing?"

    p "I'm not capable of that."

    r "I knew it."

    p "But the stakes were too high to test it."

    r "Bah. This deception will not go unanswered."

    p "Bye."

    f "Bye!"

    "Remilia leaves them alone."

    p "Get on the table. I'm going to try applying stuff to your wings."

    "She climbs on the table face-down like before."

    f "Do you know why they're getting worse?"

    p "No. Not yet. I'll try to figure that out."

    f "Ok."

    "She begins rubbing a potion into the wings."

    f "What does that stuff do?"

    p "If I'm lucky, one of them will restore your wings. But regardless, they'll help me figure out what's going on with them. I'll spare you the details."

    f "Ok."

    "She applies a few more."

    f "Hey, are you getting along with my sister?"

    p "I think so."

    f "Does she still be mean to you?"

    p "Was she mean before?"

    f "Yes. She was being harsh."

    p "Seemed normal to me."

    f "Huh. Really?"

    p "Mhm."

    "She puts vials onto a tray."

    p "Ok, that's all of them."

    f "Did it work?"

    p "No."

    f "Oh. Did you learn anything?"

    p "Only theories. The most likely thing is a form of poison. Your body is clearly not poisoned, but perhaps there is a residual effect in the wings."

    f "Poison?"

    p "I would also be curious if something specific to vampires is involved. Perhaps some form of sun magic. Unfortunately I am not familiar with how exactly sunlight affects vampires. Have you ever been harmed by the sun before?"

    f "Not really. I've had tiny moments where it touches me, but it just stings a tiny bit. That's all."

    p "Ok. Do you know if sun wounds heal normally? Like if you stuck your arm out of a window?"

    f "Uh... I don't know. That sounds scary."

    p "Ok. That would make for an interesting experiment."

    f "No!"

    p "I won't do it."

    f "Phew."

    "Flandre jumps into a chair."

    f "Now what?"

    p "I'm taking a break. Then I'll do some more research. I shouldn't need your wings for a few days."

    "Patchouli floats into her chair and floats tea over. It seemingly serves both of them on its own."

    "They drink in silence."

    "Flandre's legs slowly swing. Patchouli is still, with her eyes closing for extended periods then reopening. Eventually, they stick to Flandre for a few moments."

    p "Where did you two come from?"

    f "We come from the noble Scarlet house!"

    p "Oh, what's that?"

    f "That was our home."

    p "Right. I suppose that's why Remilia wanted to be served."

    f "She's just lazy."

    p "Hm, maybe so. What brought you into the forest?"

    f "Well... humans don't like vampires. We had to leave, or kill everyone."

    f "But now we're here! This place is nice."

    "Patchouli puts a proud hand to her chest."

    p "It is. Custom made by me."

    f "How did you make it?"

    p "Magic and imagination."

    f "You are a terrible storyteller."

    p "Fine. I studied some libraries and learned how to manipulate materials to take the shape of the ideal library design."

    f "Wow, that's cool. How did you do the magic?"

    p "It requires many years of magical study. You need to do that first."

    f "Oh. Never mind."

    "They return to their tea."

    f "Hey, do you like Remilia?"

    "Patchouli takes one more drink."

    p "I suppose she's an interesting person."

    f "Good. She can be really nice too. But she can be annoying, being mean to new people."

    p "Being cautious isn't so bad."

    f "I guess. But she's just been over-the-top since it happened. Like it's somehow her fault."

    p "Since what?"

    f "..."

    p "Oh, never mind."

    f "I can't complain, though. She makes me feel safe. I appreciate it. But she's annoying."

    p "That is—"

    "The door flies open."

    r "I'm back!"

    "Remilia flies in with a large bag."

    p "Is that one of my bookshelf covers?"

    r "Yup. A small price to pay for your deception."

    f "Hypocrite."

    r "Oh shut up."

    "She drops the bag."

    r "I have a feast. No more chickens!"

    "She opens it and reveals a mass of rabbit carcasses."

    f "Yay!"

    p "That's not what the covers are for."

    "Remilia grabs a rabbit and bites into it, blood dripping down."

    "Flandre flies over to catch blood with her hands, protecting the floor."

    f "Sis... this is someone else's home, try not to spill blood everywhere?"

    r "Blood is made to be spilled, no?"

    f "Ugh, I'm sorry Patchy, she is a terrible eater."

    p "I see. Please keep blood off the floor."

    f "I'll do my best."

    p "I was talking to Remilia."

    "Remilia tosses the rabbit back into the bag."

    r "I'm satisfied."

    f "You brought too many."

    r "We can finish them later."

    "Remilia and Flandre take a seat. Flandre grabs 2 rabbits and carefully eats."

    "The bag of rabbits vanishes."

    r "Huh?"

    p "They're in your room now."

    r "You didn't want any?"

    p "No."

    r "Oh. Ok. Your loss. That's kind of cool though, you can just teleport anything, anywhere you want?"

    p "Within my domain, most inanimate things."

    r "So you can also eavesdrop on anyone, and make your voice appear anywhere?"

    p "Not really eavesdrop. I just know which rooms people are in."

    r "Oh, good. No eavesdropping then."

    p "That would be useful, but no."

    r "How are Flandre's wings?"

    p "Wings still the same. However I have more ideas to look into."

    r "Mm, ok."

    f "The rabbits were good. Now I want to sleep."

    r "Fantastic. A proper meal must be followed by a proper rest. Shall we?"

    "They return to their room."

    r "A fridge?"

    "She opens it."

    r "There they are. The fruit of my labor. How nice."

    "She closes it."

    f "Is that all you did today?"

    r "No, I explored the area. It is very secluded, I quite like it. Plenty of wildlife to feed off of. Patchouli has a rather clever chicken trap as well."

    f "It's a cool spot to build a library."

    r "I wonder if she is capable of building one."

    f "She did. She told me all about it. Magic and creativity!"

    r "Oh. Interesting. What else?"

    f "Not much."

    r "Ah, ok."

    f "You're really curious."

    r "Eh, not really."

    f "You are."

    "Flandre jumps into her coffin."

    f "See you tomorrow!"

    r "Mm, sure, see you."

    "They go to sleep."
    
    return